      "reference": "arXiv:2201.11669 (Comput.Phys.Commun. 283 (), 2023)",
      "authors": "Liu, Xiao, Ma, Yan-Qing",
      "description": "Pedagogical massless one-loop two-point (bubble) family with off-shell external momentum $p_1^2=1$, used to illustrate the auxiliary mass flow procedure step-by-step. One master integral $I(1,1,\\varepsilon)$ is reproduced numerically through $\\mathcal{O}(\\varepsilon^0)$ by introducing the auxiliary mass $\\eta$ in both propagators, deriving the 2x2 differential equation in $\\eta$ (Eq. 2.11), expanding around $\\eta=\\infty$, propagating through regular points $\\eta_0=-i/2$, $\\eta_1=-i/4$, $\\eta_2=-i/8$, and matching to the asymptotic expansion at $\\eta=0$. The numerical result $1/\\varepsilon + 1.42278 + 3.14159 i$ agrees with the analytic answer $(-1-i0)^{-\\varepsilon} \\Gamma(\\varepsilon) \\Gamma(1-\\varepsilon)^2 / \\Gamma(2-\\varepsilon)$.",
